"As more and more businesses move to online interactions and transactions, many are looking to cut costs and increase profits. One way businesses have sought to do this has been by adopting a do-it-yourself approach to Secure Socket Layer (SSL) security. Doing so, however, puts organisations at risk of both costly breaches and loss of trust from customers and partners. Few companies have the resources and skills to create and manage SSL certificates to the level of security and reliability offered by a Certificate Authority (CA), argues Reiner Kappenberger of Symantec. As more and more businesses move to online interactions and transactions, many are looking to cut costs and increase profits. One way businesses have sought to do this has been adopting a do-it-yourself approach to Secure Socket Layer (SSL) security. Doing so, however, puts their organisation at risk of both costly breaches and loss of trust from customers and partners."
